# Flat-6 2.8 Rally – Engineering Design Notebook (Revision A)

**Project:** Daily-use automobile with rally genes – custom coupe/fastback, RWD/AWD, 1200-1350 kg  
**Engine:** Twin-turbocharged 2.8L flat-6, 95 RON, Euro 5  
**Status:** Rotating assembly frozen; piston geometry revised for squish clearance

---

# Design Change Log (Rev A)

| Issue | Original | Revised | Reason |
|---|---|---|---|
| Squish clearance inconsistency | Deck clearance = 0 mm, squish described as 1.0 mm (0.5 gasket + 0.5 piston-deck) – contradictory | Piston crown recessed 0.5 mm below deck. CRC becomes 33.5 mm. Dish volume recalculated to 9.2 cc. Squish clearance = 1.0 mm (0.5 gasket + 0.5 gap) | Resolves contradiction; maintains safe piston-to-head clearance |
| Turbo specification language | Top-level spec said “twin-scroll per bank”, manifolds were single-scroll 3-into-1, K04 listed which is single-scroll | Corrected spec to single-scroll per bank. K04 and GTX2860R remain valid candidates. | Aligns specification with actual hardware chosen |
| Compression height / dish | 34 mm CH, 12 cc dish, flush deck | 33.5 mm CH, 9.2 cc dish, 0.5 mm deck gap | Keeps compression ratio at 9.5:1 with corrected squish clearance |

